# Per-account state written by setup.py: the Bedrock Prompt Management prompt ID.
# Account-specific and recreated on every `uv run python setup.py`, so it must
# not be committed. triage.py reads it (or the RELAY_TRIAGE_PROMPT_ID env var).
prompts/.prompt_id

# Module 5: the Knowledge Base id + data-source id setup.py records so kb.py,
# compare_retrieval.py, and freshness_test.py find the KB without an env var.
# Account-specific and recreated on every `uv run python setup.py` (or settable
# via RELAY_KB_ID); never committed.
.kb_id
.kb_data_source_id

# Module 7: the deployed CloudCart MCP server's Function URL that setup.py records so
# relay/tools.py can build an MCP client. Account/deploy-specific and recreated on every
# `uv run python setup.py` (or settable via RELAY_MCP_URL); never committed.
.mcp_url

# Module 8: the AgentCore Memory id setup.py records (relay/run.py reads it, or the
# RELAY_MEMORY_ID env var) and the AgentCore Runtime ARN the `agentcore` CLI prints
# (recorded via `setup.py --record-runtime <arn>`). Both are account/deploy-specific and
# recreated on every setup / deploy; never committed.
.memory_id
.runtime_arn

# Module 9: the Bedrock Guardrail id + published version setup.py records so relay/safety.py,
# relay/llm.py, and run_attacks.py resolve `relay-guardrail` without an env var (or settable
# via RELAY_GUARDRAIL_ID / RELAY_GUARDRAIL_VERSION). Account/deploy-specific and recreated on
# every `uv run python setup.py`; never committed.
.guardrail_id
.guardrail_version

# Module 10: the agent's structured DECISION LOG — runtime output appended on every handled
# ticket (audit_report.py reads it). Even though inputs are REDACTED before writing, it is
# operational data, not source — never committed.
decision_log.jsonl

# Module 13: the submitted Bedrock RAG-evaluation job ARN marker (account/run-specific,
# written by setup.py --submit-eval, read by teardown.py to clean the job up). Never committed.
.eval_job_arn

# Module 13: non-baseline eval RUN results are runtime output (a fresh run each time). ONLY the
# committed baseline (run-baseline.json) is source; every other run-*.json is regenerated.
evals/results/run-*.json
!evals/results/run-baseline.json

# Module 11: the AWS CDK synth output (cloud assembly) the `cdk` CLI writes under cdk/.
# Account/deploy-specific build artifacts regenerated on every `cdk synth`/`cdk deploy` —
# never committed. The queue URL is resolved at call time (RELAY_QUEUE_URL env var, set by
# the CDK stack on the Lambdas, or GetQueueUrl), so there is no marker file to ignore.
cdk/cdk.out/
cdk.out/
cdk.context.json

# Module 14: the injected-fault state marker (which fault inject_fault.py has live) + the
# faults working directory (the giant ticket fixture, the corrupted-doc backup/copy, the
# staged degraded prompt). Runtime fixtures the reader injects + restores — never source.
# The post-fix verification runs (run-postfix-*.json) are covered by the run-*.json rule above.
.injected_fault
data/faults/
